senses.sense_definition: A type of citrus fruit that is a cross between a tangerine and a grapefruit, known for its distinctive bell shape and knob at the stem end.

examples.text: She peeled a juicy <w>minneola</w> for a healthy afternoon snack.
The <w>minneola</w> is easily recognized by the small bump on its top.

senses.sense_definition: Any of several towns in North America, such as in Florida or Kansas.

examples.text: They decided to move to <w>Minneola</w> to enjoy the warmer climate.
The small town of <w>Minneola</w> has a growing population.
